{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643910","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643910"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:59:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:59:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18023"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18023"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10737"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80667"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10737","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10737"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18023"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65963"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1165"},{"type":"tags","id":"1167"},{"type":"tags","id":"3949"},{"type":"tags","id":"3981"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5783"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25001"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25004"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80667","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80667"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old man presents to the emergency department following a motor vehicle accident with severe back pain. His vital signs are stable. Neurological examination is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following imaging modalities should be used first in this patient to assess for vertebral trauma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["PET scan","Plain radiograph","CT scan","Ultrasound","MRI"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECT scan\u003C/strong\u003E is the optimal choice for rapid vertebral trauma assessment. It provides detailed bone imaging within minutes, allows multi-planar reconstruction, and can be performed in patients with contraindications to MRI. The speed of acquisition is particularly important in trauma settings.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe limitations of other modalities include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlain radiograph\u003C/strong\u003E provides only 2D images and may miss fractures, especially in areas with complex overlapping structures\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMRI\u003C/strong\u003E takes longer to perform, may not be immediately available, and while is superior for spinal cord and ligamentous injury assessment, provides less detailed bone imaging than CT\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUltrasound\u003C/strong\u003E cannot penetrate bone effectively and is unsuitable for vertebral imaging\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPET scan\u003C/strong\u003E is used for metabolic imaging and has no role in acute trauma assessment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECT scanning also allows for rapid 3D reconstruction of injuries which is particularly helpful for surgical planning. An urgent MRI may be required to investigate for spinal cord injury or soft tissue/ligamentous injuries depending on the result of the CT or if there is any neurological deterioration in this patient. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["CT scan provides superior bone detail and is faster than MRI for detecting vertebral fractures.","CT scan can be performed in patients with metallic implants and is more readily available than MRI.","CT scan allows for detailed 3D reconstruction of vertebral injuries which aids surgical planning."],"references":["Cavallaro M, D\u0027Angelo T, Albrecht MH, et al. Comprehensive comparison of dual-energy computed tomography and magnetic resonance imaging for the assessment of bone marrow edema and fracture lines in acute vertebral fractures. Eur Radiol. 2022;32(1):561-571. doi:10.1007/s00330-021-08081-8","Sutherland M, Bourne M, McKenney M, Elkbuli A. Utilization of computerized tomography and magnetic resonance imaging for diagnosis of traumatic C-Spine injuries at a level 1 trauma center: A retrospective Cohort analysis. Annals of Medicine and Surgery. 2021;68:102566. doi:https://doi.org/10.1016/j.amsu.2021.102566","Kumar Y, Hayashi D. Role of magnetic resonance imaging in acute spinal trauma: a pictorial review. BMC Musculoskelet Disord. 2016;17:310. Published 2016 Jul 22. doi:10.1186/s12891-016-1169-6"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65963"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18023"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65963","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65963"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T08:30:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-22T08:30:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10737"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80667"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","na